  "texts": [
    "LLMs are also not format-invariant, with specialized reasoners excelling mostly on formats seen in finetuning.",
    "On spectral tasks, neither base nor finetuned models generalized reliably.",
    "Overall, larger models appear more robust to the above variations, but are much costlier (cf.",
    "Runtime), and fine-tuning of smaller models do not consistently improve generalization or invariance.",
    "Our study contributes evidence on the limitations of existing pipelines, motivating future work on invariance-aware training and benchmark design."
